WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.560
GTFS·X is the fastest way to build a GTFS feed.

00:00:06.560 --> 00:00:10.760
Draw new or existing routes, which snap to the streets.

00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:13.000
Then add stops.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:19.200
The stops automatically snap to your route.

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:23.059
With your stops placed, you can build a timetable.

00:00:23.059 --> 00:00:28.480
The system automatically estimates travel times on the roadway based on real-world travel times.

00:00:28.959 --> 00:00:34.400
The Visualization tab shows your headways, and the Validation tab shows errors or warnings

00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:40.000
in real-time with links that make it easy to make corrections.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:45.820
When your feed is ready, save a snapshot for publication.

00:00:45.820 --> 00:00:50.099
From the Publish tab, scroll down and click Publish Now.

00:00:50.099 --> 00:00:53.400
This publishes your feed to a stable URL.

00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:56.560
Build your feed the easy way with GTFS·X.

00:00:58.480 --> 00:01:00.480
www.gtfsx.com
